# movate runtime — local sqlite, runs cache, etc.
~/.movate/
# Ignore everything inside .movate/ EXCEPT eval baselines, which are
# version-controlled so CI can gate against them. The dance is:
#   .movate/*        ignore top-level entries (logs, sqlite)
#   !.movate/*/      but allow subdirectories to be traversed
#   .movate/*/*      ignore everything inside those subdirs
#   !.../baseline.json … except the baseline file
# (Git's rule: you can't un-ignore a file inside an ignored directory,
# so we ignore at the file level, not the directory level.)
.movate/*
!.movate/*/
.movate/*/*
!.movate/*/baseline.json
*.db
*.db-journal
local.db

# Build artifacts
*.whl
*.tar.gz

# uv: lockfile IS committed; cache is not
.uv-cache/
# uv.lock  ← do NOT ignore; commit for reproducibility

# Bicep — compiled ARM templates are derived; only the source is committed.
# Real parameter files (with KV references / live env values) are env-specific
# and never committed; only the .example template is tracked.
infra/azure/main.json
infra/azure/**/*.json
infra/azure/*.bicepparam
!infra/azure/main.bicepparam.example
scripts/deva-curl/.env
my-sandisk-agent/
openai-feedback.md

# Deva onboarding artifacts — generated locally with live URL + bearer
# baked in (via scripts/build-deva-ppt.py + the sed pipeline against
# docs/deva-endpoint-smoke-guide.md). Sent to Deva via DM, never via
# git. The committed source-of-truth lives under docs/ with
# placeholders; these are the build outputs.
*.pptx
deva-onboarding.md
deva-onboarding.pptx
